# Code Style & Change Discipline

> Canonical charter: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md). Path-scoped instructions: `.github/instructions/`.

## Change scope

- **Smallest correct change only** — no unsolicited refactors or drive-by edits.
- **Static multi-page architecture stays static** — no SPA / framework migration unless explicitly requested (`AGENTS.md` §6).
- **PR-only workflow** — no direct commits to `main`, no force-push.

## Dependencies & verification

- **Do not add new dependencies without asking** — check GitHub Advisory DB before adding anything new (`AGENTS.md` §7).
- **Preserve all existing tests** in `tests/` (`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` lists 205 tests in the architecture doc; run `npm test` before marking done).
- Before `npm test` / `npm run validate`, delete `playwright-report/` and `test-results/` if present — they can cause false positives.
- **Honest verification** — state what you ran vs. what you assumed; do not claim tests you did not run.

## Output quality

- **No placeholder TODOs** in shipped output — working code only unless follow-up is documented in the PR.

## JavaScript

- Vanilla ES modules; no new frameworks; `camelCase`; focused modules under `src/lib/`.
- **Safe DOM:** `src/lib/safe-dom.js` (`escape`, `safeHref`, `safeTel`, `el`, `clear`); prefer `node.replaceChildren()` over `innerHTML = ''`.
- **DOM-safety baseline must not regress** — CI blocks new `innerHTML` / `outerHTML` / `insertAdjacentHTML` / `document.write` sinks.
- **Python:** entrypoints add `scripts/python/` to `sys.path`; relative-import `utils.*`.

## CSS

- Use canonical tokens from `styles/global.css` (`--color-*`, `--surface-*`, `--space-*`, `--text-*`, `--radius-*`, `--shadow-*`, `--ease-*`, `--duration-*`). No hand-picked hex/rem where a token exists.

## Strings & motion

- Every user-visible string in `src/config/translations.js` — never hard-code UI text.
- **Bilingual EN/AR parity** — all user-visible copy ships in both languages.
- Every animation respects `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

## Arabic / RTL (required on every layout change)

- All user-visible strings go through `src/config/translations.js`.
- Layouts must work with `dir="rtl"`. Test **360px** minimum.
- Mirror chevrons, arrows, progress bars; preserve number formatting.
- Copy must read like natural Arabic, not English-shaped Arabic.
- **RTL layout must be preserved on every change.**

## Core commands (local)

```bash
export JWT_SECRET=<random 32+ char string>    # required for server/tests
export ADMIN_PASSWORD=<any string>            # required
export ADMIN_ACCESS_PIN=<6+ digit PIN>        # optional PIN gate

npm install
npm run dev
npm test
npm run lint
npm run validate
npm run build
npm start   # Express on :3000
```
